<br>
I've been following/participating in this discussion on and off since back in the days when the best BP in the game for AC was the BEBP from LGuk or rubi from CT (i.e. before PoF and thorny vine was even put in), and the primo (only) warrior board was on eqstratics.  Rather than add, I'd just chip in that what Graal says above is fully consistent with everything I've seen and parsed so far.<br>
<br>
I would like to see/do some analysis on the effects of the new AAs.  In particular, I'm thinking that you could SERIOUSLY reduce the DPS taken if you picked the right set of skills...<br>
-mitigation/avoidance (CS/CA, innate defense, lightning reflexes), obviously<br>
-tactial mastery (significantly fewer ripostes, makes a big differernce vs. mobs that hit for 1k+).<br>
-stalwart endurance (less damage taken while stunned, which seems to interfere with avoidance skills).<br>
-max out Agi + planar power, up to new cap of 305ish<br>
-max out resistances, to avoid elemental damage if/when verant decides to give them to mobs (I'm guessing it's in the elemental planes right now, only a guess tho- should hear for sure soon since people are keeeeling stuff there now).<br>
<br>
Toss in the high end skill modifier items (+% dodge, parry, riposte, and maybe someday block) and I think you'd see a BIG, tho streaky (due to RNG) reduction in average DPS taken.  It seems like the same RNG seed, which might be zone-wide and is apparently changed each tick or so, is used for many differnent calculations during combat.  Simple probability sez that multiple small percentage changes can add up quite nonlinearly if they are applied serially, especially if they are entangled and not discrete...<br>
<br>
I think. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
