<br>
You can't compare mobs from different expansions, it won't work. Each expansion's ubers and higher levels are tuned to characters of the corresponding level. So AoW versus the Frenzied Ghoul from LGuk is a worthless comparison.<br>
<br>
You can't compare mobs of different levels. The Orc in EC is green while the AoW is deep deep red at 55. So tell me, do you actually know that at level 3 you only need 600 or 700 or whatever incredibly low number to reach the orcs soft cap? No, you do not.<br>
<br>
The devs stated publicly that a soft cap DOES exist. This was at a fan faire Q&amp;A. I wish I could remember which, but I can't and I'm not going digging. The dev stated that AC is made up of 3 components. One of those components has a hard cap, one has a point of dimishing returns, and the last is a free range number. He said this translated to a baseline softcap, not a per mob softcap.<br>
<br>
You can not claim that the soft cap exists only per mob when even your anectodal evidence is un-provable. The contention has been made that the reason you can't cap against the AoW is because no one can get the gear to get high enough. But tell me, how do you know that you aren't already at the cap and that even with 2200 points of AC you won't get any noticable returns? The simple answer is that you don't. The AoW whoops your ass primarily because he's red. <br>
<br>
At 65 he's a joke, at 60 he's brutal, at 55 he's an impossibility, regardless of your AC. <p>Shelrabbi Hassida<BR>
